# ${PROJECT_NAME}

Project rules. Applies to every Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, and Aider turn that runs inside this repository.

This file lives at `<root>/dev/CLAUDE.md`. The same content is duplicated to `<root>/dev/AGENTS.md` for tools that follow the AGENTS.md standard. Do not edit these files by hand — they are regenerated by `bootstrap.sh` from `templates/CLAUDE.md.tmpl`. Edit the template (or the `rules/*.md` files it references) and re-run `bootstrap.sh --config .my-harness/.config`.

## Output language

`LANG=${LANG}`. All user-facing strings (TSDoc, error messages, commit messages, PR descriptions, doc updates) MUST be in `${LANG}`.

## Mandatory reading

Before any code change, every agent MUST read these rule files. They are the single source of truth shared across all tools:

- `.my-harness/rules/tdd.md`                — Red / Green / Refactor, AAA, $LANG test names
- `.my-harness/rules/jsdoc.md`              — TSDoc on every export, no inline comments in function bodies
- `.my-harness/rules/hono-clean-arch.md`    — domain / application / infrastructure / interfaces dependency direction
- `.my-harness/rules/drizzle.md`            — `drizzle-kit generate --name <descriptive>`, no `push`
- `.my-harness/rules/design.md`             — Lucide Icons only, WCAG AA, prefers-reduced-motion
- `.my-harness/rules/nix-pure.md`           — All tool execution via the per-worktree devshell wrapper
- `.my-harness/rules/no-hardcoded-secrets.md` — env vars / SOPS only

## Project layout

```
${ROOT}/
├── .bare/             bare git clone
├── main/              production worktree
├── stage/             staging worktree
├── dev/               default working worktree (this is where Claude Code starts)
│   ├── CLAUDE.md      this file
│   ├── AGENTS.md      copy of CLAUDE.md (read by Codex CLI / Cursor / Aider)
│   └── .my-harness/
│       ├── rules/     rule files referenced above
│       └── scripts/   harness shell scripts
└── lanes/             feature worktrees (created by /harness-team-lead)
    └── feat-<id>-<slug>/
```

